This paper is about a tool for utilizing and processing embeddings, which are commonly used in natural language processing (NLP) applications. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.CL (Computation and Language), which focuses on NLP and related topics. The paper also discusses the performance of the tool, which suggests that it may belong to cs.LG (Machine Learning) or cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). Additionally, the tool involves efficient manipulation of large amounts of data, which could fall under cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms). Finally, the paper mentions out-of-vocabulary lookups, which could relate to cs.IR (Information Retrieval).
